caption: My favorite spot for tasty Japanese food. fell in love with this place from the 1st taste.
japanese food, mmm, super delicious. Nice place to think about business. Definitely worth going back to. The place has an awesome atmosphere. They have so many great reviews for a reason.

We used to go to Sakanaya (sushi place at Green St) but due to COVID-19, their dine-in is close. Miga partnered with Sakanaya and offers the exact same sushi menu. This place offers dine-in option. They adhere with social distance and staffs wear mask. The sushi tastes the same and my experience has been great so far. Great ambience, great service, great food! You can even make reservation online. Best sushi in town.
One of my all time favorite restaurants. Really good food, good atmosphere, and good service. Everything is very high quality.
One of the best restaurant around Champaign

The food is really good but do not trust them with your events. I double checked everything with them twice few days in advance but there was no communication between the staff. On the day of the event, there was only one waitress for the whole restaurant who said she had no clue about the reservation. She asked us not to order any cocktails because she couldn’t make any. She also forgot one of the orders and she was very slow probably because she was the only waitress for the whole restaurant. They also charged us for a private room fee which was free according to their website.
Love the food and atmosphere. Absolutely great food and the staff were all friendly!
Their sushi boat is a must have! love the interior

Love the sushi boats and great desserts!!
I would give 0 star if I could. Worst service ever! Have been sitting there for 20mins without being served! Unbelievable!

I used to think this place was too uppity, but it's more reasonable than a Chicago restaurant and their food is always spectacular! Definitely a good spot for a date night or taking clients out. But be sure to get a reservation! They fill up fast!
Good food and atmosphere
The galbi steak is really good
I love the food and vibe here. All sashimi is fresh. And the funky jazz music matches the chill vibe of this great place.
My meal at Miga was excellent. Fresh, elegant presentation and delicious. Waiter was pleasant and efficient. The atmosphere in the restaurant is modern, but comfortable. Will definitely go again
Delicious food. Pricey but delicious.
had the hungry roll. very good !
Incredible food, service and atmosphere! Highest end seafood in the Champaign area. Check out their sister restaurants Sakanaya and Naya, would highly recommend all three.
Delicious and our waiter was knowledgeable about the menu and very helpful.

I’m not sure what was going on at miga tonight. There was a very strange vibe today. The hostess seemed terrified. Our waiter, who we have had before and has always been very friendly, was very obviously flustered. Our food took much longer than normal but still seemed like it sat around for a while before being served to us. There was a man, maybe a new manager, because I did not see the female manager who is usually there, awkwardly walking around but maybe serving tables at the same time? I can tell the staffs reaction to him was not a positive one. It was VERY tense. The only person working I saw smile the entire time we were there was a girl carrying an arm full of dishes that I passed in the hallway on my way to the restroom. I’m almost embarrassed I brought friends here today. I promised them this isn’t the typical feel of miga. I don’t know what caused whatever was going on tonight but I hope it doesn’t continue. Maybe I’ll give them a few months to cool off.
5 stars for service, interesting selections (enjoyed the calamari), ambiance and great food. Creme brûlée is good but could be creamier. Another place to keep going back to.
Always a great meal. Exceptional service.
Our favorite restaurant in town. Always a great dining experience. And our kids (who only love McDonald’s) share that sentiment...
Food was super fresh and tasty.
Very unique. Love the ambience, atmosphere and meal selections

Miga is one of the most luxurious restaurants in the Urbana Champaign I've ever been to! The interior has recently been remodeled and it’s soo beautiful. I’ve always liked the contemporary atmosphere and, most importantly, the quality of the food is AMAZING without a doubt. I had sushi and sashimi combination with Katsu and both have been my favorites since years ago! Some may think the price can be a bit costly, but seriously, the quality of the food justifies everything!  p.s. the server was very nice and knowledgeable :)))
Great place. The sushi here is great. I totally recommend the Toro roll
Great atmosphere. Cool tasty dishes.  Nice experience
Every time I call regarding bookings or anything related, the hostess has been extremely rude.   Each time she has been unwilling to help with anything.  Very disappointing for sure.
The service was as good as the d er luscious food!

House soy sauce is very sweet, didn't pair well with the sushi. I thought this would be like Sakanaya but a step up, but only 1 of the 3 rolls I got was very good. Will probably just stick to Sakanaya from now on
Top notch from the service to the food. It is expensive, but worth it.
Best in town. Sushi is great, the tuna steak is fantastic! Little pricey but will leave happy with your meal. Will go back!
Celebrated a 1st year anniversary there and everything was superb! Food was awesome. Sake was perfect. Server was fantastic!
Great sushi spot to take a date!
Perfect Food is great.
Astonishingly high quality sushi (no ocean in sight!). HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!
ripeye * kimchi....  wow  great
Excellent food. Great service. The ribeye was the most tender I'd ever have.

Very impressed with Miga! The service was outstanding and the food is very well made. The fusion is impressive, the soy sauce is the best, and serving size is good. I plan to return and would recommend to anyone.

The bibimbap is very good with the seared salmon and their Gyoza is pan fried perfectly and does not taste like it's been frozen like other places I've been to. The decor is super modern and clean and, from the drinks that I've had, are very well done.
Delicious! Great service
Delicious tuna steak

Miga is one of the best restaurants in town. The ambience is upscale but comfortable. It is perfect for special occasions, such as our 27th anniversary dinner. Miga is Asian fusion, and by that I mean Korean combined with nouveau Italian and French. We had some of the best white fish I've ever had (butterfish) and the scallops, which were huge and very tasty. We start things off sharing the wasabi salad and some finely mixed drinks. Everything was excellent, and the service was on point. Highly recommend Miga for your next occasion.

Miga is an enigma. Its tucked away in the shadow of Distihl, within the same building. The atmosphere and decor is very stylish but the seating is lacking. Its recommended to make a reservation if you want an actual table. Bar seating is available, if you are ok with being surrounded by everyone else food; limited counter space makes this difficult. The food itself is high quality, although a bit pricey.
Delicious food and excellent service!
Geisha roll is so beautiful and delicious
The geisha roll is amazing!!
Sushi, so good. I give this place two thumbs up. Service is typically above par. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I loved.
Had a delicious Ribeye and the starters as well as cocktails are great, too.

If you are looking for a classy date night in downtown area, MIGA is the correct choice. Inside is decorated with modern and contemporary styles with bar seats, rooms, and tables that can accommodate large parties. Food is the fusion of Korean and American styles along with a sushi menu. It is a bit pricey, but the dining experience was exceptional.
Awesome atmosphere, friendly and knowledgeable staff, excellent cocktails, and of course delicious food. A downtown Champaign dining experience that is not to be missed.
Very tasty food every time we go and always very friendly staff!
Great service.  Fair prices for quality.

This is my first time writing a review on a restaurant and I can say that my experience at Miga was great. Wonderful atmosphere, welcoming hosts, great servers, and exceptional plating. This is something hard to find at Urbana-Champaign.
Pretty good. Not the best I've had, but better than most in town. Sea Bass app was pretty good and the rolls were decent. I would come back to try some of the other dishes.
Such a nice atmosphere. Every worker is very welcoming and most importantly,  food is very delicious!
Excellent! !!!

Korean without kimchi.  Salmon doused in sugar sauce. Way too much salt on the seafood.  "Bottles" of beer that are .2l.  "Seasonal greens" = salad in February.  There's better places to spend your time, let alone your money.  Finally, charging for substitutions? Really?  This was once a very good place. Sadly something has changed.
Excellent in all areas!

Miga is one of the most high-end restaurants in Champaign, Illinois. The interior of Miga is a piece of art. The food at Miga is Asian fusion food so it contains various tastes. My favorite food at Miga is their rolls and sushi. The food is really good in general, but the rolls were shockingly delicious. The decorations of the food were really pretty too, and it made me want to eat the food more. The fish on the rolls and the sushi weren’t frozen fish, so I could eat the sushi fresher! I’ve been to a lot of Japanese restaurants, but I have never tasted food like Miga’s. I sincerely recommend this restaurant to people who want to visit Champaign or live in Champaign but have never been to Miga. I really suggest this restaurant!
Definitely the place to go when it’s a special occasion or holiday. The food may be a little bit pricey but it’s definitely worth it.

(Translated by Google) I am surprised that you can eat this fresh sashimi in American soil. I'll go again next time I go to Champaign ~  (Original) 미국땅에서 이렇게 신선한 회를 먹을수 있다는게 놀랍네요. 다음에 Champaign 갈 일있으면 또 가야겠네요 ~
Best sushi in Champaign!

This was our first visit to Miga, and unfortunately did not leave a very good impression. It seems Friday nights might not be the night to eat at Miga. The hostess was extremely rude and unwelcoming, and made us feel very uncomfortable. We walked in at 8:49 pm and she said the kitchen closes at 9 and all of the customers are finishing up. That’s it, nothing else. A very awkward moment transpired where we had to ask what time is it and will we be able to order? I tried to lessen the awkwardness by saying maybe another night, but my date insisted we give it a shot and so we ordered drinks and a few sushi rolls as soon as we sat down. When our server came over, we explained what had just happened and he said he still had orders in, which clearly shows all of the customers were not almost finished. We enjoyed the ambiance, drinks and sushi, but unfortunately the unfriendly welcome at the door before 9 pm ruined this first time experience for us at Miga.
Dessert was l1t
Food is very delicious, and worth what you pay!!

We visited the place on a Friday night with a group of friends and we were hoping for a "no drama" experience. The hostess was extremely unwelcoming and rude to our group. Her reaction to our group was quite embarrassing.  At first, she told us the table was available.  Next,  she shared that it was not available.  After i provided her with my feedback about her rude service,  she did not apologize or explain her behavior. Instead,  she confused me further. It seemed like there was room at the bar and in the restaurant. We clearly saw some open tables.  We left shortly after her ambivalent and rude service and took our business to a another upscale restaurant with better service. I will never go back to that place again ! Especially,  not If i want to have a relaxing evening with friends.

Bibimbap is simply salad. Not cooked at all.
Great Food and presentation. Excellent service with jared. Go with the unicorn dessert.

One of the best dining establishments in Champaign. Interesting menu (korean/american fusion, with some sushi and italian mixed in). Interesting menu with some really awesome food. Great cocktails too! Can't miss choices: scallops; steak; geisha roll, pork bun.

I eat a lot from a lot of different places. The steak was by far the best steak I have ever eaten. The sushi rolls (Mexican and Fuji Mountain) were superb. The sweetcorn croquettes were to die for. The drinks were amazing.  The service was top notch!  I would recommend this to anyone!

Something changed since the first visit about a year ago. The black napkins used to be folded to represent a tuxedo. They now lay folded flat. Presentation means a lot to guests. Water was poured in glasses at unattended tables. That seemd kind of unsanitary to me. And it wasn't cold.  The menu was very limited unless you liked sushi and/or nigri. But three out of the four of us weren't big sushi fans. It was an ok but pricey experience and I don't think I'll be back anytime soon. Our waiter Derek was woderful though.
Came for group dinner. Sushi is very good. Nice atmosphere!

Went to Miga Saturday night and had one of the best Ribeye steaks ever! The Mojito was fresh and authentic and the service was fantastic! We also had the seviche which was excellent and also tried 2 very different, and excellent flavor combinations. We loved them both! This was the perfect place for "date night".

Awesome high end creative Asian American fusion! The recent addition of sushi was a brilliant idea !  Wonderful decor.  Everyone on staff welcomes you and the owner came to our table to say hello. Great experience!

I was really impressed by the atmosphere of MIGA immediately. I was even more impressed sitting at the bar and watching the chef do his craft. It was like watching an art form- I would definitely recommend trying out this spot. I got the Nigiri Chef special and every piece was delicious. We also got a Sushi "dessert"- more of a night cap. This was very special and unlike anything else I have ever experienced. This is a truly unique experience, especially if you allow the chef to dictate your meal. However, as many of the other reviews have stated, be prepared to dig into your pocket for this night out.
Has potential, but needs a focus on consistency.
Delicious food, but took unbelievably long, and service was subpar. We ordered, ate, and payed as quickly as possible, and the whole meal took over 2 hours.
Once of the best restaurants in Champaign.
Excellent sushi!
Outstanding service and food.

One of the best restaurants for fine dining in Champaign. Located right in the heart of downtown, Miga is a modern fusion of Asian and American food. Their fish and sushi dishes are super tasty. Each and every dish on the menu is thoughtfully prepared and the presentation is top-notch. They have a really nice private room which you can reserve for a large party. The service is very friendly and environment is upscale. Miga is a perfect place for a date or professional meeting. I'm proud to have taken many of my good friends here.

This place had some of the best sushi that I have ever had. The service was amazing and scheduling my dinner reservation for me and my girlfriend's anniversary was stress free. The menu is a bit pricey, but if you look past that, you will find an excellent place to have a nice dinner.
Get the sashimi! Infinite mochi
Really good sushi, can compete in Champaign

Probably the only restaurant that you will be able to catch the luxurious vibe in Champaign as it literally feels like dining at a 5 star hotel not only with its extraordinary food but with the professional customer service. Best quality restaurant in Champaign in every category for sure. 💯
Best sushi in Champaign!
Very good food for my 1st time ever there. The staff was very helpful and professional.

This is my favorite restaurant in Champaign!    The ambiance, service, and food is ALL phenomenal..ALWAYS!  I went for the new sushi menu on Thursday night and I am obsessed!  I recommended the GEISHA ROLL!  ENJOY! Ask for Teale as your server!

Completely terrible. The waitress cheat customers when customer inquiry some information of unfamiliar dishes from them. Waitress usually hook customer to order dishes with the highest price and never pay attention with the quality of their dishes. Steak is completely not chew-able, but waitress still described it as a perfect steak when she hooked customer to order it. After customer figured out the meat quality of their steak is bad and not chew-able, then waitress just found any excuses to skip away from the guilty of their misleading.
Expensive but very nice. Drinks are well selected too (but pricey). Would go again for a special occasion
The food was great.  It is a pretty upscale place but worth it.  Make sure to have a reservation or just be ok with sitting at the bar.

Some of the best Sushi I've ever had! I live in Denver but come to Champaign a few times a year for business and I always have dinner at Miga. This time I happened to stumble in on their second night to offer a full sushi menu. I'm not gonna lie...at first I was bummed because I was really looking forward to the sea bass which is no longer on the menu.  I decided to stay because the owner had already come by to greet me and brag about the new sushi menu. I was skeptical (and so sad I wasn't getting miso sea bass!) but all that went away when I tasted my first dish, the yellowtail crudo. OMG it was truley amazing and so so fresh. From there I had the Mexican Roll (tuna, cilantro, I can't remember what else), then the maguro nigiri. I really can't say enough as to how amazing it all was. I loooove sushi and love to put my fancy sushi dinners on the boss' credit card all over the country. I can't say how pleasantly surprised I was to find such an amazing place, especially in Champaign. Miga will still be my go to place when I'm in town.
That filet au poivre may have been the best thing to ever enter my mouth.

This place is quite nice for a really romantic date night. Ever since they got a new chef the menu is not quite as good as it use to be but the food is still very tasty. Service is fantastic. Every time I make a reservation and inform them that it's to celebrate an anniversary they play light romantic love music. I think that's above and beyond for any restaurant to do.
The boo bim bop was excellent. The ravioli were spicy and delicious.
Consistently amazing food. I have yet to have a bad experience here since they opened almost three years ago. High end food and service at affordable prices...and entirely without pretentiousness.
Good service, great food and cocktails.  Private rooms for larger Groups.
If you are love fine dining and gourmet food then this is the place! Wonderful experience!

Miga is the best upscale dinner in Champaign. They have a small menu of Asian-inspired dishes that changes somewhat regularly. Service is very good, the space is beautiful, and their cocktails are creative and excellent. Also, check out their brunch - prices are low for the quality and the food is delicious. This is definitely a place I come back to regularly.

Top restaurant to go on special day not only in Champaign downtown, but in whole Illinois! This restaurant constantly updates its menu, and all of the menu are delicious! I've went to this place several times with my girlfriend, and this restaurant is my girlfriend's fave as well. The servers are nice and professional, and if you ask, they can describe you the menu in a very accurate way. Definitely recommended.
Total 5 star restaurant. Excellent place to go and dine with your friends or family during your downtown visit. The place is exquisite and classy and trust me, every dish is to die for  :)
Good cocktails, modern decor, really good food

Starters Scallop - Tastes very good 4.5/5 beef SSAM (beef with romaine wrap) - Fabulous 5/5  Main Menu Angus Galbi Rib-eye Steak - A bit salty but tastes very good 4/5 White Butter Fish - Salty, but tastes good 4/5  Drink Coedo Hefeweizen - Excellent Hefeweizen

I've never been disappointed with Miga. I have always had an extremely memorable and positive dining experience here. I also had a birthday Private party here with over 80 guests. Not many restaurants could have executed a flawless event like the staff at Miga did. The manager, Jen, was awesome to work with and very flexible with all of my crazy ideas and requests. The party went off without a hitch, and every other time I've dined here, it's always been perfect.

I've been living in Champaign Urbana area since 2008, and Miga is by far the best quality restaurant. I am somewhat stingy on rating restaurants, becuase I strongly believe that there is always something to be improved. However, every aspects of Miga were above my expectations.  First of all, servers. They have been trained really, really, well. They studied thoroughly for all the menu, and they could give me all the details about how the foods are prepared and cooked.  Next, cleanliness. I usually go to the restroom to check the cleanliness. Restroom is easy to clean compared to the kitchen. If restroom is dirty, you can expect that the kitchen would be the same. Miga passed my restroom test, which not many restaurants in Champaign do. Not only that, general cleanliness of the overall area is very clean.  Third, environment. Let's say you have your significant other with you and would like to bring them to a nice place. Miga is the ONE. Some restaurants think that dim lighting is the only way to enhance the mood. Well, aren't you tired of eating your food without being able to see them? Miga has decent lighting but still could enhance the romantic mood, which is not at all easy thing to be done.  Last but not the least, the food itself. Well, I've said enough about other aspects, and you know what I would tell you about the food quality. Besides, you wouldn't believe my words unless you go and try them yourself.  It is hard to find a nice place where everything is perfect but, I am telling you, Miga will satisfy every aspects of you are looking for.  Added note: Miga also has awesome brunch menu served on Sundays!!

Miga has been our favorite go-to restaurant for special nights the past couple of years.  We always look forward to starting our meal with their outstanding Wasabi Bacon Cesar salad.  Last night, we were disappointed to learn that they have changed their presentation.  Instead of being served chopped and mixed in a large wooden bowl,  the salad is now served as an intact half a head of romaine lettuce, with the dressing and sun-dried tomatoes, drizzled on top.  A chunk of pork replaces the slice of bacon.   When we asked for plates to share this salad, we were given 6 inch small plates that didn't even comfortably hold a slice of this ungainly monster of a "salad".  Bad idea, go back to the way you were..

I want to love Miga so badly. I've eaten here 4 times now. The first time was in the spring 2015. The food was good, but the prices seemed out of sync with the actual quality of the food. Still, it felt good enough that I wanted to try again. I ate here 2 times in 2016, and just ate here again tonight. The ambience is great! The food is edgy, so some flavor combinations are unexpectedly amazing and others are not for me. But tonight, the service just disappointed me. We had come from a wine tasting, and we just didn't want to order a drink right away. Perhaps that annoyed our server. We ordered two appetizers and a main dish to "start with," and our server, again, seemed annoyed. We ordered a sashimi salad (the chunks of sashimi tuna and salmon were just too big - we were expecting thin slices), Miga crunch fries (seriously the best thing on the menu!), and halibut. The food took an unreasonably long time to come out, but the temperature was right. Our server didn't come back to check on us until we were done with the meal, and we didn't feel like ordering another plate (scallops with tomato basil foam) and waiting even longer. I watched her drink coffee at the bar and visit other tables, but didn't come back to us. She wasn't rude-  just annoyed, I guess. When she took our plates, she barely said thanks, she just acted like we weren't even there. I just don't get it.

Upscale dining. Great food quality. Great atmosphere. Exclusive feel to it. Prices are "good" for what you get on most dishes, considering the ingredients and options. I would rate this as one of the highest quality restaurants in this area.
The level of service was above and beyond great and we really enjoyed the private room for a Birtday celebration.

I have never been to a restaurant where the servers are seemingly forced to recite every ingredient of the dish as they present it, when we're well away of what we ordered and just wanna eat. It's obviously annoying for the servers too.
Pretty tasty, but a bit pricey. If you want something you can't get anywhere else in the area then this would be a good choice.
Amazing food and service
Food was amazing and staff handled my allergies just fine. However the wait to order and then for food was very long. There were only 3 tables and in total we waited probably an hour.

Vies for the best restaurant in town honors.  It is the best if your looking for edgy Asian-fusion (Bacaro if you are looking for interesting traditional fare).  Interesting cocktails and decent wine lists.  Wasabi caesar a great salad,  scallops on pork belly with bacon foam a winner, as is the smoked duck dish.  Caution: all of the dishes have a bit of spice so might not be the place for you if you're a no spice person.

Miga is an impressive space - urbane, new wave, polished, clean. The food  were superb - tasty as well as artistically concocted.  However, services left a lot to be desired.  The art of hospitality was not consciously ingrained in the servers.  For example, food were served without serving spoon/fork and while we waited hot food got cold because our server seemed to have forgotten until being asked again.  I would think that owners and operators of modern restaurants would train their service helps better.  The long wait for drink orders or other requests seemed unreasonable since the restaurant was not very busy when we were there.  The food arrived at reasonable time but the small lack of common sense service seems incongruous. If the idea is to draw out the wait time for anything, then it was well done.  If the idea is for servers to be inefficient in their job then they hit the mark. Please do better because I like the place and the food a lot. And I don't want to leave a grudging tip. I'm willing to reward good job well done.  I want to see Miga around 20-30 years from now here in Champaign, Illinois.
Awesome restaurant with an Asian influence.
I have been to Miga several times and I love it! The entire vibe of the restaurant is so relaxed and classy. Not to mention the food is fantastic!
Such a great place to eat.  Loved the flavor of every dish.   The Ramen salad was delicious!

City nightlife atmosphere-modern and edgy.  Old B&W movies on the wall.  Very slick, in a good way.  New age American fusion Korean fare.  Fun presentation.  Thumbs up!  If you're not adventurous then you might take a pass...

I have been to several asian fusion restaurant in Chicago downtown and Evanston area. I would like to say this place is definitely one of the top asian fusion restaurants in midwest area. I love their modern environment with artfully prepared and curated food!! I ordered Angus Galbi Rib-eye Steak with Wasabi caesar salad and it was just amazing.. I'm not trying to help their business.. this is just 100% truth and I strongly recommend you to try their food..!!!
Good service, delicious Asian-fushion dishes!  I had the Salmon entrée and my husband had the tuna and both are perfectly cooked.

The setting is very unique; bench style seating, projector playing old movies on one of the walls.  The food was amazing! I had the Tuna steak and I am experiencing a case of FOMO (fear of missing out), don't know if I can pass it up next time. Menu is fairly small and simple side and prices are a bit higher here but they make up for it in the quality of their dishes.  Service was attentive and knowledgeable. Would definitely recommend to the foodies out there.

Food and service are both fantastic. While the decor's dark colors and wood textures are relaxing in this modern restaurant, some items on the menu can be too salty or too sweet, but should be suitable for most American palates.  One thing that bothers me is their choice of knife, actually. Most knives handles follow the direction of the blade, but the one Miga uses are actually horizontal handles. As visually delightful as they are, they are unintuitive to use and actually had some difficulty because whenever I held the handle naturally, the blade would actually face left or right because it's at a ninety degree angle to the handle.
A bit pricey, but classy, great take on some Korean food, excellent service. A wonderful place to celebrate an important event.
Food and service both fantastic! :)
Best fish I've had in years.

I made a special occasion reservation for Miga about two weeks in advance of the date and noted on my request that I had a gluten allergy. When my companion and I arrived, we were seated and waited about 5 minutes for the server.  When the server visited the table for the first time, I told him I would need some assistance with the menu as I had a gluten allergy. The server, a bit hostilely, told me that the the chef and the restaurant would not serve anyone with celiac disease and if I had a problem with that he would have the manager come speak with me. I let him know that I had made my allergy clearly known on the reservation request and that I was unclear why the restaurant had not notified me.  My companion and I left, feeling angry and embarrassed. We walked past the hostess station where he was conferring with the hostess and manager. None of them spoke to us as we walked through the door.  There is nothing on Miga's website or OpenTable profile to indicate this limitation. If there were, I would not have chosen to dine there.
One of my favorite places in downtown champaign. Great atmosphere and better food. The steaks are amazing.

A very lovely addition to the dining options in downtown Champaign. Miga is definitely on the pricier ends of things, but well worth it. The staff is super friendly and very knowledgeable about the menu and willing to offer suggestions. I ordered the ceviche as a starter and didn't receive what I expected, so definitely ask away before finalizing an order. First time experience was nice, I look forward to coming back.
Upscale atmosphere! Very classy! Love the food and drinks. Service was awesome. There is not reason not to be a Miga Regular!
It was a great space but the food was o.k. super awkward service because there were no other patrons.

Delightful addition to downtown dining!  Pleasing, open, contemporary atmosphere perfect for conversation.  Setting is great for couples, small groups and business meetings.  All of our menu selections were delicious.  Seafood was perfectly prepared.  Their signature mixed drink was refreshing.  Wines pair well with their menu.  Something on the menu for everyone from the meat lover to the vegan.  Both Asian and French influences are well represented.  We are planning to be regulars!  Can't wait till they are open for lunch.
